Sentencas: Redox stable SOFCs with Ni-YSZ cermet anodes were developed for electrolyte supported design (electrolyte thickness: 170 mu m).
Titulo: Redox Stable Solid Oxide Fuel Cells with Ni-YSZ Cermet Anodes Prepared by Polymeric Precursor Infiltration

Sentencas: Redox stable Ni-YSZ anode was prepared by infiltrating polymeric NiO precursor into pre-sintered porous YSZ layer (similar to 10 mu m thick) followed by reduction ex situ.
Titulo: Redox Stable Solid Oxide Fuel Cells with Ni-YSZ Cermet Anodes Prepared by Polymeric Precursor Infiltration

Sentencas: Polymeric precursor infiltration technique yielded a Ni-YSZ cermet microstructure with nanosized Ni particles coating the surface of porous YSZ.
Titulo: Redox Stable Solid Oxide Fuel Cells with Ni-YSZ Cermet Anodes Prepared by Polymeric Precursor Infiltration

Sentencas: Low temperature processing of nanostructured Ni-YSZ cermet resulted in the reduction of internal stresses between Ni/NiO coating and YSZ skeleton during the redox cycling process.
Titulo: Redox Stable Solid Oxide Fuel Cells with Ni-YSZ Cermet Anodes Prepared by Polymeric Precursor Infiltration

Sentencas: Electrolyte supported SOFC prepared with Ni-infiltrated anode showed a power density of similar to 0.315 Watt.cm(-2) and a highly redox stable anode (reduction of power density less than 1% after 15 redox cycles) in humidified forming gas (10%H-2-90%Ar).
Titulo: Redox Stable Solid Oxide Fuel Cells with Ni-YSZ Cermet Anodes Prepared by Polymeric Precursor Infiltration
